    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-03-17T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-03-17T08:00:00-05:00" n="302"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d302">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/9122: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hare</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-03-17T15:00:00+02:00"
                            >March 17, 1941—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 18—6:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>121. It has been learned from a British official source that Berbera<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d302fn1">In British Somaliland.</note> was captured as a result of a
                    fleet operation at 7 a.m., March 15, but thus far news of the event has not been
                    released. Control of this port will give the British a much better supply line
                    for their East African forces than from Italian Somaliland ports and will also
                    facilitate planned utilization of air bases in British Somaliland and East
                    Central Abyssinia as soon as advance troops are able to occupy those areas.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hare</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
